column3: Title

نیروی کششی اسمی نبشی زیر چه اندازه است؟ پیچ ها با قطر 25 میلی متر و جنس فولاد مصرفی ST37 می باشد. Fy=2400 (kg/cm2 و Fu=3700 (kg/cm2.  مقاومت برشی پیچ ها را 16000 (kg/cm2) در نظر بگیرید. دانشجویان محترم به‌غیراز انتخاب گزینه ی صحیح حتماً می بایستی طریقه ی محاسبه ی گزینه ی صحیح را نیز نوشته و ارسال نمایند. عدم ارسال روند محاسبه ی صحیح نمره ای در بر نخواهد داشت.

برای اتصال تیرچه فولادی به تیر فولادی نشان داده‌شده در شکل زیر بر اساس کنترل گسیختگی قالبی ناشی از نیروی برشی (V) در طراحی به روش حالت حدی حداقل ضخامت جان تیرچه به کدام یک از مقادیر زیر نزدیک تر است؟ (قطر محاسباتی سوراخ ها را برابر با D=۲۰ mm  و Fy=۲۴۰۰ kg/cm۲ و Fu=۴۰۰۰ kg/cm۲ و Vu=۱۸۰ kN در نظر بگیرید). دانشجویان محترم به‌غیراز انتخاب گزینه ی صحیح حتماً می بایستی طریقه ی محاسبه ی گزینه ی صحیح را نیز نوشته و ارسال نمایند. عدم ارسال روند محاسبه ی صحیح نمره ای در بر نخواهد داشت.

column3: Concrete is characterized by the type of aggregate or cement used, by the specific qualities it manifests, or by the methods used to produce it. In ordinary structural concrete, the character of the concrete is largely determined by a water-to-cement ratio. The lower the water content, all else being equal, the stronger the concrete. The mixture must have just enough water to ensure that each aggregate particle is completely surrounded by the cement paste, that the spaces between the aggregate are filled, and that the concrete is liquid enough to be poured and spread effectively. Another durability factor is the amount of cement in relation to the aggregate (expressed as a three-part ratio—cement to fine aggregate to coarse aggregate). Where especially strong concrete is needed, there will be relatively less aggregate.  The strength of concrete is measured in pounds per square inch or kilograms per square centimetre of force needed to crush a sample of a given age or hardness. Concrete’s strength is affected by environmental factors, especially temperature and moisture. If it is allowed to dry prematurely, it can experience unequal tensile stresses that in an imperfectly hardened state cannot be resisted. In the process known as curing, the concrete is kept damp for some time after pouring to slow the shrinkage that occurs as it hardens. Low temperatures also adversely affect its strength. To compensate for this, an additive such as calcium chloride is mixed in with the cement. This accelerates the setting process, which in turn generates heat sufficient to counteract moderately low temperatures. Large concrete forms that cannot be adequately covered are not poured in freezing temperatures.    Due to the above text, which option is true?
column5: The strength and durability of concrete are two major characteristics of concrete material.
column7: پایان ترم زبان تخصصی-26-3-1400 ساعت 13:40 تا 14:30

In ordinary structural concrete, the character of the concrete is largely determined by a water-to-cement ratio. The lower the water content, all else being equal, the stronger the concrete. The mixture must have just enough water to ensure that each aggregate particle is completely surrounded by the cement paste, that the spaces between the aggregate are filled, and that the concrete is liquid enough to be poured and spread effectively. Another durability factor is the amount of cement in relation to the aggregate (expressed as a three-part ratio—cement to fine aggregate to coarse aggregate). Where especially strong concrete is needed, there will be relatively less aggregate.  The strength of concrete is measured in pounds per square inch or kilograms per square centimetre of force needed to crush a sample of a given age or hardness. Concrete’s strength is affected by environmental factors, especially temperature and moisture. If it is allowed to dry prematurely, it can experience unequal tensile stresses that in an imperfectly hardened state cannot be resisted. In the process known as curing, the concrete is kept damp for some time after pouring to slow the shrinkage that occurs as it hardens. Low temperatures also adversely affect its strength. To compensate for this, an additive such as calcium chloride is mixed in with the cement. This accelerates the setting process, which in turn generates heat sufficient to counteract moderately low temperatures. Large concrete forms that cannot be adequately covered are not poured in freezing temperatures.    Due to the above text, which option is true?
column5: The strength and durability of concrete are two major characteristics of concrete material.

column3: Of the two surface seismic waves, Love waves—named after the British seismologist A.E.H. Love, who first predicted their existence—travel faster. They are propagated when the solid medium near the surface has varying vertical elastic properties. Displacement of the medium by the wave is entirely perpendicular to the direction of propagation and has no vertical or longitudinal components. The energy of Love waves, like that of other surface waves, spreads from the source in two directions rather than in three, and so these waves produce a strong record at seismic stations even when originating from distant earthquakes.  Due to the above text, which option is correct?
column5: Love waves of an earthquake felt in the near field and far-field

column3: Of the body waves, the primary, or P, wave has the higher speed of propagation and so reaches a seismic recording station faster than the secondary, or S, wave. P waves, also called compressional or longitudinal waves, give the transmitting medium—whether liquid, solid, or gas—a back-and-forth motion in the direction of the path of propagation, thus stretching or compressing the medium as the wave passes any one point in a manner similar to that of sound waves in air. In the Earth, P waves travel at speeds from about ۶ km (۳.۷ miles) per second in surface rock to about ۱۰.۴ km (۶.۵ miles) per second near the Earth’s core some ۲,۹۰۰ km (۱,۸۰۰ miles) below the surface. As the waves enter the core, the velocity drops to about ۸ km (۵ miles) per second. It increases to about ۱۱ km (۶.۸ miles) per second near the centre of the Earth. The speed increase with depth results from increased hydrostatic pressure as well as from changes in rock composition; in general, the increase causes P waves to travel in curved paths that are concave upward.  Due to the above text, which option is correct?
column5: P waves inside the ground travel faster than the surface the ground

P waves, also called compressional or longitudinal waves, give the transmitting medium—whether liquid, solid, or gas—a back-and-forth motion in the direction of the path of propagation, thus stretching or compressing the medium as the wave passes any one point in a manner similar to that of sound waves in air. In the Earth, P waves travel at speeds from about ۶ km (۳.۷ miles) per second in surface rock to about ۱۰.۴ km (۶.۵ miles) per second near the Earth’s core some ۲,۹۰۰ km (۱,۸۰۰ miles) below the surface. As the waves enter the core, the velocity drops to about ۸ km (۵ miles) per second. It increases to about ۱۱ km (۶.۸ miles) per second near the centre of the Earth. The speed increase with depth results from increased hydrostatic pressure as well as from changes in rock composition; in general, the increase causes P waves to travel in curved paths that are concave upward.  Due to the above text, which option is correct?
column5: P waves inside the ground travel faster than the surface the ground

column3: سد کارون 4، در استان چهارمحال و بختیاری و شهرستان لردگان قرار دارد. این سد بر روی سرشاخه های اصلی رودخانه کارون از جمله رود بازفت و رود کوهرنگ احداث شده‌است.در حال حاضر از این سد می‌توان به عنوان بزرگ‌ترین سد دو قوسی خاورمیانه نام برد. ارتفاع این سد ازپی 230 متر می باشد. در صورتی که 150 متر از مخزن سد پرآب باشد، برای یک المان در عمق 100 متری مخزن کدام گزینه صحیح می باشد؟
column5: دایره موهر برای این المان به صورت نقطه می باشد.

column3: درخردادماه 1400 یک مخزن گازوییل در پالایشگاه تهران دچار آسیب شد و تمام گازوییل موجود در آن مشتعل شد. با فرض ارتفاع این مخزن برابر 12 متر و قطر دوازده متر، میزان تنش افقی در راستای جوش در ارتفاع 6 متری را محاسبه نمایید. ضخامت را 3 سانتیمتر در نظر بگیرید. وزن مخصوص گازوییل را 840 کیلوگرم بر متر مکعب در نظر بگیرید.
